  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version (output of `vyper --version`): v0.3.1\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\nminimal repro:\r\n```python\r\nevent Foo:\r\n    message: String[100]\r\n@external \r\ndef foo():\r\n    log Foo(\"fewer than 68 chars\")\r\n```\r\nresults in the following traceback\r\n```\r\n  File \"/home/charles/.venvs/vyper/lib/python3.8/site-packages/vyper-0.3.2+commit.27cec1b5-py3.8.egg/vyper/codegen/events.py\", line 80, in lll_node_for_log\r\n    assert data.typ.abi_type.size_bound() == _maxlen, \"bad buffer size\"\r\nAssertionError: bad buffer size\r\n```\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\nrelax the assertion to say `<=` instead of `==`",
